description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Do you have a passion for teaching? Do you want train staff to understand and deliver care for our patients that they deserve which distinguishes a highly trained workforce to deliver the best quality of patient care?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated individual who brings excellent clinical knowledge and experience in Theatre practice. You must be a role model and extremely organised, supportive and able to communicate effectively. You will work clinically alongside other team members and departments to ensure best practice is aligned by sharing of information across departments.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be responsible for the educational development of all ODPs, Nurses, newly qualified practitioners and students within the Theatre department. With support from lead Theatre Practice Development Nurse / Practitioner, you will be involved in the planning and delivery of specialist education and training of all areas of Theatre practice.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameNatalie NewmanJob titleMatronEmail addressnatalie.newman@walsallhealthcare.nhs.ukTelephone number01922 721172 ext 7474&lt;/p&gt;
